page.title: 09Mud and Shingle Shoreline
page.content: The mud and shingle has less vegitation and much{more man made {debris}lying around. On the higher slopes near the sea wall there is a line of{flotsam and jetsam}from passing ships and coastal industry. Several{waste pipes}empty into the river here. Plants of the higher shingle include:Teasal,Oxford Ragwort,Wild Carrot and Hoary Cress. Wide areas lower down covered daily by the sea have little vegetation on the shingle and cobbles but the{soft muds} have Bladder Wrack,Spiral Wrack and Grass Kelp. The different zones of vegetation are clearly seen but the natural features are spoilt by the rubbish (tin cans,plastic bags and broken boxes ect),the waste pipes and the jetties that stick out into the river.
